Page.PageName: Steps 8 & 9- Fault Function Test, Dose Reading Test

Text.Value: At the end of the testing sequence, a blinking "9" will appear indicating the RATE function is operational.
If a flashing "8" or a flashing "L" appears on the display, refer to the troubleshooting procedures.
Perform Dose Reading Test:
• Press and hold the DOSE button until a blinking (dotted) rectangle appears on the LCD screen, release the button.
• The blinking (dotted) rectangle will be immediately replaced with the accumulated dose reading.
The display for the ALARM setting of "AUD" and/or "VIS" may or may not be lit depending on previous usage and device settings.
